{"/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_chapel_ver01/data/sn87055779/00517017656/1923122001/0247.xml":{"full_text":"SOUTH BEND NEWS-TIMES\nMorning\u2014Evening\u2014Sunday\nJ. M. STEPHENSON.\nPublisher.\nSEED.\niger.\nBOTD OTTH LET,\nEditor.\nMember:\nAmerican Newspaper Publishers* Association\nAudit Bureau of Circulation\nMOBXINO EEITION.\nr*>\u00ab I* exclusively entitled to th* w tor\nn* lorniiottfl Prm la exclusively entitled to tba w tor\n\u25a0MoUmUoi of lU news dispatches credited to It or sot\nMinrlM credited in the morn log edition of this paper, and\n\u20221m tan local new* published herein.\nFull Leased Wire Service\nUnited News\nEVENING EDITION.\nFull Leased Wire Service\nUilted Press International News Service\nSIM. (Broaeh BuSaaff)\nTEEMS Or SUBSCRIPTION:\nCarrier Borrleo\u2014\nMorning and Bondar, per week\nEvsalag and Sunday, par week..\nwith Bandar, ona raar\nDali/ (oltkao edttwa)aad Sonda y on rnral route*, ono rear JO.00\nJlL ethers by mall.-\nEntered at South Band Pont Offlet a* Second Ona* Mall.\nAN INDEPENDENT NEWSPAPER\nDECEMBER 20. 1923\nWHO ARE BEST PEOPLE?\n\"Ha oorved the beat people.\"\nIt la ths prohibition director for thlo state talk\ning. He lo before the pardon board where one\nHooo is asking for clemency.\nHose, It appears from the records of his case,\nsold liquor, forbidden by law, to state house of\nficials and to men of wealth at the state capital.\nHe bad the \"high class\" trade.\nTile comment of the prohibition director 1s inter\nesting ss revealing his viewpoint and it is not\noriginal with him. It seems to be the view of\nmany prohibition directors and enforcement officers\nIn many states and In most cities.\nIt reveals, rather naively, that there are dis\ntinctions \u201camong law breakers in the minds of those\ncalled upon to enforce this law.\nFor It la quit* as much against the law to buy\nas to aell liquor in these days, so It la somewhat\nnew to And an official who doscrlbes those whom\nhe ts supposed to prosecute as the \u201cbest people.\u201d\nThose who believe that the enforcement of this\nparticular law Is necessary, not because they believe\nIn It but because discriminations are producing a\ndisrespect and a disregard for all law, will be ln\nteres ted In the fact that the officers of the law be\nlieve that men may violate any law and still be\nHated aa among the best people.\nThere was a time when violation of any law\nbrought with It certain ostracism and criticism.\nThere was a time when a man could not openly\nbe known as the patron of criminals or conspirators\nto violate the law and be received In decent circles.\nThe thing called society has been builded around\nthe theory that those within its sacred circles\npossess powers of leadership and example and that\nthe welcome to. that circle Is desirable because\nIt gives a certain credential to respectability.\nThat day Is, apparently, over, when the chief\nSleuth for a particular crime classifies the patrons\nof orlmlnals.\nIt la a rather dangerous statement. Had the\ndeclaration been made that the law Is enforced\nagainst the man whose pocketbook affords only\nmoonshine and Is tolerated for those who can af\nford tho present quotations on the \u2018real stuff,\u201d\nenforcement officers would at once declare that It\nWas wet propaganda, put out to hamper the law\nand to undermine opinion for the law.\nFor an enforcement officer to declare that a\nperson may traffic with a bootlegger and retain his\nstanding In society and business is to give official\nsanction to this very charge of discrimination.\nUnerringly It points to tho chief trouble in enforc\ning the law. As long as men may trade with law\nviolators and retain /their respectability, as long\nas there does not attach the social ostracism and\nobloquy which adheres to every other criminality,\nthe way,to complete enforcement will be difficult.\nIt Is perhaps, temporary. In anothe'r generation\nsuch a statement will be impossible. It will take\nthat long to build up the same sentiment behind\nthis lgw which must be the bulwark of every law\nthat regulates society. But when that day comes,\nthere will be no officials at pardon hearings eulogiz\ning the,patrons of crime.\n-o\nFORGOTTEN HISTORY\nA distinct service was rendered to this community\nby former Secretary of Commerce Redfleld when\nhe recalled to the members of the Knife and Fork\nclub last night some pages of our history which\nare forgotten.\nThat Holland, France and Spain declared war\nagainst England In order to help the Revolution\nIs not generally remembered.\nThat Catherine of Russia refused to supply sol\ndiers to King George Is not emphasized.\nThat a Prussian staff officer trained the army\nOf Washington la a page that is turned rapidly.\nMoat of all, that this government offered to re\ndeem its paper currency Issued during the war\nat one cent on the dollar and was unable to do\nso because seventy millions of dollars of It had\nbeen used as wall paper, may suggest a ray of\nhop* for the return of prosperity to nations whose\ncurrency is now worthless.\nThese facts may at least give rise to a spirit of\nluiciniu sjui^aiujr iui vfuiia juxiua which are 2Q\ntrouble.\nIf this, the wealthiest nation, could rise from ao\nlow a atate of poverty aa repudiation of its cur\nrency to Its present eminence, there Is hope that\nother peoples by using the same methods of work\nand Industry may reach destinies of splendor.\nIt seems to be a human trait to forget the day\nOf adversity as soon as possible. It la very human\nto forget the aid obtained In an hour when aid\nwas needed. Gratitude Is not so common a virtue\nas to be taken for granted.\nLet It be hoped that whatever aid Is given Is ex\ntended to peoples whose character and whose pur\npose are as good or as great os waa that of the\ncolonial fathers who accepted and benefltted by\nthe kindnesses extended to them.\n\u20141-o\nTHE FAMILY JAR\nA good-sized family row, now and then. Is the\nsafeguard for the family.\nThat is the rather interesting theory of the\nlatest dabbler In psychology, who by the way la\nalso a physician and 11119 written a book or so on\nthe relation between health and the state of mind.\nThose who have looked Upon squabbles at home\nas tragedies have been mistaken. If you accept his\nword for It. They are the explosions which clear\nthe home atmosphere.\n\"Tou may depend upon It,\" he remarks, \u201cths\nhusband and wife who have It hot. and heavy for\nwhile^and clear up the atmosphere are much more\nhealthy physically than the couple who never have\n\u2022ven a tiff and are always in accord,\n\"The woman who doesn't assert herself and take\nher husband In hand once in a while is really\nnothing mors than a moron. Men never have given\nwomen anything, except what they wanted them\n\n\nto have, without a struggle. And they never will.\nMen aren't built that way.\n\u2018\u2018This la true In the home a* well ae In political\nand social life. Women have to know what they\nwant and then light for It. If they don't develop\na epine for themselves eventually they become\ncolorless, vague, negative.\n\u201cThe clinging vine never has done anything for\nherself or for her race. And she Is bound to find\nherself in time with nowhere to cling. Economic\npressure, If nothing else, is forcing every Individual\nto fight for himself, and those who can\u2019t will fall.\"\nAnd yet, there does come a recollection of a\ntime when the clinging vine trait In womanhood\nheld high place in the Ideals of literature. But\nprobably the men who Wrote the books with such\nwomen as heroines didn\u2019t know.\nImagine the theory carried to Its logical conclu\nsions. Think of eulogizing lack of harmony as a\nvirtue. Picture the police and divorce Judges\ncalmly looking over the wreckage of ill temper\nand assuring those who came for relief that they\nhad simply Indulged In a necessary act of letting\noff suppressed mental steam.\nImagine the marriage service revised so as to\npledge a dally, weekly or monthly quarrel as the\npillar of Its permanency.\nPsychology Is a wonderful^ study. Some psy\nchologists seem to deserve a different adjective.\no\nREADING THE STARS\nVery Interesting prediction, the one you read In\nthis newspaper by an astrologer who looked at the\nposition of the stars and said that Mr. Coolidge\nwill have a short term as president.\nAstrology was called the first science. It was\nalso the first religion, when men worshipped the\nstars and believed that'they controlled human\ndestinies.\nThe number of men and women who still believe\nthat all lives are determined by the hour of birth,\nthat every act and circumstance Is fixed by the rela\ntive positions of stars and planets, Is somewhat\nastounding in an age that has airplane^ and radio.\nEvery year many men and women have their\nhoroscopes read by those who have worked out\nsystems of meanings for the stars and who spend\nhours in calculating the probable affect of Venus\nand Mars and Batura upon human temperaments.\nPredicting political results from these stars has\nbeen a favorite diversion, Interesting because such\npredictions are always flavored with the personal\nopinions of the astrologer.\nFor a real political prediction, the opinion of\nSenator James Watson, who does not read the\nstars but who knows many political workers, will\nbe a much more valuable guide as to the nom\nination.\nIf you desire to know what is likely to happen\nat an election, go to any picture show which ex\nhibits the photographs of national leaders and\nlisten to the applause that comes from the audience.\nThat is a much safer guide than the prophecy of\nthose who believe that some mysterious force comes\nfrom the stars, 4nany millions of miles away, to\ncontrol the events of every human life.\n.,.0\nTHE USEFUL CITIZEN\nOutstanding in significance of all the intimate\npictures of great men at Washington given by\nWilliam Hard, veteran newspaper man, is one of\nSecretary of Commerce Hoover.\nHe sqys that the title only begins to describe\nhis duties or his Influence.\nIf the labor department is in trouble, it is Hoover\nwho responds to a presidential call for aid.\nIf the state department reaches a blind wall,\nit is Hoover who is called upon for advice and a\nway out.\nIf the agricultural Interests are threatened,\nHoover comes to the rescue with a plan.\nIf the treasury department needs an idea, it is\nHoover who gives it. t\nThis is the information given by a man who has\na reputation for knowing the Inside of things at\nthe nations,! capitol and who has attained eminence\nfor his ability to discover the truth about men and\naffairs.\nIt might seem that in the ordinary course of\nevents a man yvho has proven so valuable to every\ndepartment of government might be mentioned, at\nleast casually, for the one position in which all\nthese Interests are combined.\nFour years ago Mr. Hoover had a large follow\ning for the presidential nomination. The people\nwho were for him did not know what his politics\nwere. Mr. Hoover took some time to decide the\nquestion and finally let the people into the secret\nthat he was a Republican\u2014too late to get past the\npoliticians.\nThe one reason the invaluable man at Washing\nton does not reach the big job is that he lacks\nthe thing called political acumen. The one cure\nfor that situation is for the people to take a hand\nand eleot their own president instead of turning\nthe Job over to politicians.\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014o\nChicago couple eloped in an airplane. That\u2019s the\nway these days. They fly high at first.\no\nNebraska scientists claim they have found another\nlost race. Tou can get plenty at a race track.\nI\nTODAY\u2019S TALK\nBj George Matthew Adams.\nSETTING AN EXAMPLE\nOur growth, and our happiness as well, Is regu\nlated largely by what we set before us as some\nthing to strive toward.\nWe are all imitators.\nWe read an inspiring book, or phrase, or we see.\nan uplifting example in some character\u2014and we\nImmediately want to produce or be in some way\nworthy of these things, thoughts or people, so that\nwe may be helpful and Inspiring, too.\nAnd there is none of us so simple or unworthy\nbut someone else is watching us and seeing in us\nsomething that 1s sure to be imitated by them.\nHow quickly a calm, beautiful personality radiates\nits worth. And how quickly those about such a\none seek to take upon themselves the virtues and\nbeauties of such a character.\nThere is nothing that brings out the buds and\nflowering of one\u2019s heart like knowing that you are\nbeing of use in this world by inspiring someone\nelse, either through what you say or what you do.\nEven in silence we are examples\u2014for what we\nare radiates much farther at times than what we\nactually speak in words.\nA happy life or personality uplifts everyone it\ncomes in contact with. Let such a one merely\nwalk down the street, and every passerby is made\nbetter, whether he realizes it or not.\nI pass by the cold bronze figure of some noted\nman or woman. Immediately my mind sets at\nwork certain messengers, who go to this book or\nthat, to this incident or that, and carry back to\nmy consciousness impressions of a noble character\nwhose example makes me want to be better.\nRemember this\u2014someone Is making you their\nTheTow/Babel\nDill Armstrong\nFRIENDS, BUSINESS IS PICKING UP; SOUTH BENDERS\nAPLENTY, MILLERSBURG, IND., NORTH LIBERTY AND\nMANY OTHERS FURNISH WEDNESDAY\u2019S FIREWORKS;\nWANT TO BUY A GOOD HORSE (SEE BOTTOM OF\nCOLUMN)\nTHREE HUNDRED AND FIFTY\nEIGHT DOLLARS!\nThat was Wednesday\u2019s total, con\ntrlbufed by loyal readers of The\nTower toward furnishing a Merry\nChristmas for the hundreds of poor\nfolks, who are wards of Ray Bird's\nCity Rescue Mission.\nThis makes a total of $2,384.69\nsubscribed to this altogether good\ncause thus far. Not bad, brothers\nand sisters, not bad! But there\u2019s\nstill a>lot of money needed to put\nover the kind of a Christmas Tower\nfolks will want these poor unfortun\nates\u2014particularly the little kiddles\n\u2014to have. So let us again urge that\nIf you haven\u2019t already done so, to\nsend In your check without delay.\nWe\u2019ll guarantee your check In\nvested In this proposition, will give\nyou more happiness than you have\nhad before in many a day.\nNow just a word as to what this\nmoney and all this talk Is for.\nOf course you nearly all know\nabout It by this time, but for the\nbenefit of those that came In late,\nwe will repeat some of the impor\ntant facts. This fund is for the\npurpose of giving a Christmas cele\nbration to the poor folks, who are\nwards the year around of the City\nRescue Mission, whose sky pilot is\nthe well known Ray Bird. Every\npenny contributed to the Tower of\nBabel\u2019s Christmas fund will go for\npresents, clothing and fuel for these\npoor unfortunates who would not\nbe able to distinguish Christmas\nfrom the Fourth of July if it wasn\u2019t\nfor the generous readers of the\nTower.\nAs last year the more .than 600\nchildren attending the mission will\nbe tendered a turkey dinner in ad\ndition to the Christmas joys they\nwill receive from the Tower fund.\nDirectors of the Rescue mission will\nbe the hosts at the dinner to be\nserved next Monday noon at the\nOliver Hotel.\nSounds good, doesn\u2019t it7 You talk\nabout the old standard of the dollar.\nWhy folks, every dollar invested in\nthis cause will give you more happi\nness than you ever thought was in\nthe world before.\nSo comb the cob webs oft the old\ncheck book and send in your contri\nbution today. The sooner you send\nit the better. Your name and your\ncheck will stir others into giving.\nKick in Brothers and Sisters, Kick!\nMaybe you\u2019ll enjoy The Tower\u2019s\nlatest mail as much as we did, so\nhero goes:\nBUI:\u2014\nJUST A BIT\nTO HELP A BIT.\nJAMES ALWARD.\nNo. Liberty, Ind., 12-18-23.\nEditor Tower of Babel,\nSouth Bend News-Times.\nDear Sir: Please credit the\nList of Contributors\nWEDNESDAY\u2019S DONATIONS.\nMutual Benefit Ass'll.\nWyman\u2019s store .S 50.00\nlions Club 100.00\nJ. S. Alward. 1-00\nAI, the Pool Hound. 5.00.\nFred F. Fatter. 2.00\nJas. J. Armour. 10.00\nA. M. Knox, Jr. 1.00\nJ. M. Stndebaker, Jr..100.00.\nStudcbaker Foundry Good\nWill Club .50.00\nGolden Mann .10.00\nHarry Armstrong. 1.00\nA Friend 2.00\nBelle of Buchanan. 1.00\nH. W. Eldredge. 10.00\nKankakee Woman's Club of\nNorth liberty 10.00\nZion\u2019s Reformed Sunday school\nMlllersburg, Ind. 5.00\n\"Total, Wed. Dec. 19 ...$358.00\nPreviously Reported.2,026.09\nGrand Total.$2,384.69\nKankakee Woman\u2019s Club with\n$10.00 as a contribution to the\nTower\u2019s Christmas Fund.\nYours truly,\nMRS. BERT MORRIS,\nPres.\nMlllcrsburg, Ind.,\nIfeo. 17, 1923.\nDear Sifs:\nThe Junior Boys of the Zion\u2019s\nReformed Sunday school of this\nplace would like to share their'\nXmas with others less fortunate,\nso enclosed find a check for $5\nwhich they wish to be used for\nRay Bird\u2019s Xmas dinner.\nResp.,\nMRS. S. A. LANTZ, Teacher.\nt South Bend, Ind.,\nDec. 19, 1923.\nBill Armstrong,\nIn care of Greatest Newspaper j\non Earth,\nSouth Bend, Ind.\nDear Bill:\nOnce again I would like to do\nmy bit toward making It a very\nmerry Christmas for the little\nones.\nYours with a lot of pupple\nlove, I am\nBELLE OF BUCHANAN.\n(Editor\u2019s Note:\u2014We can see where\nwe won\u2019t have no home no how if\nthe Business Manager happens to\nrun across the above perfumed note\nfrom The Belle of Buchanan.)\nWANT TO BUY A HORSE?\nAnybody want to buy a good horse?\nFunny question, you\u2019ll say, coming from The Tower of j\nBabel engaged in raising funds for the proper kind of a Christ-\nmas for the wards of the City Rescue Mission, but maybe you\nwon\u2019t think it\u2019s so funny when you hear the rest of the story.\nGeorge F. Duffy, of Chicago, is in the city and wants to sell\nhis horse, a very fine one, buggy, harness and complete equip\nment and last night he offered the entire outfit to The Tower of\nBabel for the Christmas fund. j\nRay Bird\u2019s poor folks at the mission get all the proceeds of\nthe sale, if some one wants the outfit.\n\u201cDo we hear a bid?\u201d\n\u201cFifty we are bid; do we hear a fifty-five; fifty-five, do we j\nhear sixty\u2014and so on.\u201d\nFolks if there\u2019s any of you needs a good horse, here is your j\nopportunity to get one and at the same time help the Tower\u2019s\nChristmas party.\nThis classified ad Mr. Duffy Is running in The News-Times\ndescribing his proposition:\u2014\nGOING south, will sell at sacrifice, black (fast) mare, bugrgy,\nharness and all equipment; splendid delivery or roadster.\nAddress H-42, care News-dimes.\nDo we hear an offer?\nThe News-Times Bureau of j\nQuestions and Answers\u2014\nQUESTIONS ANSWERED.\nTon can re* an answer to any question of fact or Information by writing to\nThe News-Times Washington Bureau, 1322 N. Y. Aye., Washington, D. C., en\nclosing 2 cents in stamps. Medical, legal and love and marriage advice will\nnot be given. Unsigned letters will not be answered, but all lettera are con\nfidential and receive peraonal replies.\nQ. When was war between Rus\nsia and Turkey declared?\nA. April 24, 1-877.\nQ. Can you give me names of\nsome of the great men of Asia in\nhistory?\nA. Timur, Genghis, Khan, Barber,\nAbkar, Jehangir, Shah Johan, Con\nfucius.\nQ. How many animals have been\ninspected by the U. S. government\nsince tho passage of the meat in\nspection law?\nA. Since Oct. 1, 1906, when the\nlaw- went into effect, the total ani\nmals inspected up to the close of the\nfiscal year June 30, 1923, was 1,002,\n640, 044.\nQ. What Is the altitude record\nfor a hydroplane?\nA. Jean Laporte, French aviator,\nis reported to have just established\na new altitude record for hydro\nplanes. Height 5,535 meters, or 1,299\nmeters higher than the previous re\ncord held by Lieut. Harper of the\nU. S. Navy.\nQ. How many hones are there in\nthe human body?\nA. Two hundred, exclusive of the\n32 teeth. The skull has 22; the trunk\n54, the upper extremities 64, and the\nlower extremities 60 bones.\nQ. Have the deaths from al\ncoholism fallen off since pre-prohi\nbition days?\nA. Deaths from alcoholism In the\nU. S. per 100,000 of population from\n1913 to 1921 are as follows:\n1913 6.9\n1914 4.9\n1915 4.4\n1916 5.8\n1917 6.2\n1918 i 2.7\n1919 c. 1.6\n1920 1.0\n1921 1.8\nQ. Are 'there any artificial lan\nguages?\nA. Esperanto and Volapuk are\nartificial languages.\nQ. Who was it who said, \"Don't\ncheer, boys; the poor devils are dy\ning!\" and what was the occasion?\nA. Capt. Philipps, of the Battle\nship Texas, at the Battle of Santi\nago, during the Spanieh-American\nwar, when Cervera\u2019s Spanish squad\nron was destroyed.\nQ. What baseball player holds\nthe most baseball records?\nA. Ty Cobb. He started last sea\nson, his nineteenth year, with a life\ntime batting average of .372, higher\nthan that of any other American\nLeague player of ten or more years.\nHe holds the records for most games\nplayed In American League; Ameri\ncan League record for total hits; bat\nting .300 or better for seventeen con\nsecutive seasons, equaling Hans Wag\nner\u2019s major league record.\nQ. What is an armadillo?\nA. An American mammal having\nan armor-like shell covering.\nQ. Who was Becky Sharp?\nA. A character in Vanity Fair,\nby Thackeray.\nQ. Is it true that whale meat is\nnow used as food, and if so, how is\nit cooked?\nA. Tea, whale meat is quite eat\nable. The meat resembles beef in\ntexture and appearance and venison\nin taste, but nevertheless has a dis\ntinctive flavor of its own. It can be\ncooked in innumerable ways. The\nfollowing is the recipe for cooking\nWhale meat: Cut the whale meat in\nto individual steaks and dip each\nsteak in salted milk, then in finely\nsifted dry bread crumbs. Rub each\nwit-h the juice of a grated onion;\nplace on an oiled pan, sprinkle with\na little olive or other oil on top, and\nput in a very hot oven for 10 min\nutes. When nicely browned, remove\nfrom the oven and serve immedi\nately.\n'The stops of*a thousandl\\jslful Girts.\nQPymris Christmas Suggestions\niw acr\nStore Open Evenings Until Christmas\nBeautiful Gift Rugs\nA gift for the house which will be appreciated by the whole family and give\npleasure at Christmas and for years to come is a beautiful rug. There are orien\ntal rugs with wonderful soft richness of coloring and silky sheen which grows\nsofter and richer with the years of wear. These some from far off Turkey and\nChina. Then, too, there are the rugs made in our country which are also beau\ntiful and durable.\nChinese Rugs\nThese lugs with their distinctive colorings,\ntexture and designs in blues, rose and taupe.\nWoven into them are Chineso figures of\nflowers, birds and beasts. Sizes 1 ft. 10 ins.\nx 3 ft. 6 ins., 2/i feet x 6 feet, $32 to $100.\nr Belouchistan Rugs\nBelouchistan Rugs are so soft and silky\nthat some of them are fine enough to use for\ntable scarfs. They have blending rich or\niental colors which will add luxurious beauty\nto any room. Sizes are 2x3 J/\u00a3 feet and 2 Yi\nx 5 feet. $25 to $50.\nHartford Saxony Rugs\nHartford Saxony Rugs are well known\nfor their high quality and beauty of de-.\nsign. There are modern designs and col\noring as welt as reproductions of oriental\nmotifs, taken from world famous ruga in\nnational museums both here and abroad.\nThey are not only beautiful but because\nof the unusually fine materials used in\ntheir making they will withstand the\nhardest wear. Sizes are varied, from\nH/2 inches x 36 inches to room size\nrugs from AYl ft. x 7Yl ft. to 9 ft. x 18 ft.\nSee Page 10 for other\nWyman Gift Suggestions\nWe Still Have Time To\nFrame Your Pictures\n\nCHRISTMAS\nChristmas Cards\nFramed Pictures\nStandard Frames\nPicture Cards\nCandles\nCandle Sticks\nArtists\u2019 Paints\nTHE I. W. LOWER CO.\n120 N.*Michigan St.\nOpen Evenings\n\ni\n\nBig Xmas Money\nRaising Sale\nWatches, Diamonds,\nJewelry and Xmas\nGifts. Save than 15\nto 25% by walking\nnp 18 steps to\nThe John Harris Store\n104 X. Michigan St.\nOver Clark\u2019s Itataorant and\nCar Station\nDR. L. K. BUNCH\nSurgeon Chiropodist\nDR. MARIE B. CONNOR\nAssistant\nFOOT SPECIALISTS\nHonrs: I A. H to 11 M.\n1 P. M. to S P. Ji\nTnesdtj, Thursday and Saturday\nEtcdIocs, 7 to\n411 J. M. S. BoOdint\nfinatb Bf\u00ab4\nWE WILL LOAN\n$10 to $300\nAT LEGAL INTEREST\nOlf WAGES, FURNITURE\nPIANOS. AUTOS, Em\nto tha loborlm* bulb taiploya4 at\naatiaptoyad.\nCm 7\u00ae\u00ab it to talk tai p|\nMonty tbla way T\nWa favlta yoa to eaaaa la.\nIM)IANA FINANCE Ca\nTaba wJZS\nOpyaalto OUtav Hatol","height":"30960","width":"23848"}}
